==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elaboration
<hw>E*lab`o*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>elaboratio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧laboration</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of producing or refining with labor;
improvement by successive operations; refinement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The natural process of
formation or assimilation, performed by the living organs in animals and
vegetables, by which a crude substance is changed into something of a
higher order; <as>as, the <ex>elaboration</ex> of food into chyme; the
<ex>elaboration</ex> of chyle, or sap, or tissues.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elaborative</ent>⟦br⟧
